description:
The dataset provides a harmonised, field- and farm-level representation of agricultural land use across European Union Member States. It compiles and standardises Integrated Administration and Control System (IACS) data, including crop types, land use information, and farm-level attributes, into a consistent spatial database. The data are processed and harmonised using reproducible workflows implemented in Python and R, enabling cross-country comparability of agricultural land use patterns at parcel and farm scales.

The dataset supports analysis of agricultural land use intensity, spatial distribution of crops, and farm structure across Europe. It includes both raw and harmonised outputs, with additional derived variables and metadata to facilitate modelling and comparative studies. The accompanying documentation describes data processing methods, harmonisation steps, and validation procedures ensuring consistency across regions and time periods.
The dataset is archived on Zenodo (https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.14230620
), with accompanying code and processing workflows available on GitHub (https://github.com/clejae/europe_land_iacs_prep
), and is further documented in the Europe-LAND project deliverable D2.1 on IACS inventory harmonisation (https://europe-land.eu/wp-content/uploads/D2.1-IACS-InventoryHarmonization-Documentation_v1.1.pdf).
